FLORIDA BOARD OF BAR EXAMINERS RE: E.P. CASE NO.: SC18-359 Supreme Court of Florida. MARCH 27, 2018

A True Copy

John A. Tomasino Clerk, Supreme Court

Upon consideration of the Report and Recommendation filed by the Florida Board of Bar Examiners, it is ordered that the Board's recommendation is disapproved by the Court. The Court would approve a conditional admission of no less than three years. The applicant shall not be admitted to The Florida Bar without *634the condition of a three-year probationary period.
